HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 323
BY REPRESENTATIVE EDMONSTON
A RESOLUTION
To commend the Louisiana Court Appointed Special Advocate (CASA) programs and
volunteers; to recognize the contributions of CASA volunteers across the state; to
honor James Barse of CASA Jefferson as the Volunteer Advocate of the Year; to
honor Ja'Nika Stanley of Capital Area CASA as the Heart of Advocacy Award
recipient; and to designate Wednesday, May 27, 2026, as CASA Day at the Capitol.
WHEREAS, the people of Louisiana pride themselves on giving back to their
communities and contributing to the improvement of the quality of life of all citizens; and
WHEREAS, CASA programs in Louisiana, in association with the National
CASA/GAL Association for Children, speak for the best interests of abused and neglected
children; and
WHEREAS, CASA volunteers are trained community members appointed by a judge
to advocate for the best interests of children who have experienced abuse or neglect and who
are involved in the child welfare system; and
WHEREAS, Louisiana CASA programs and volunteers provide a powerful voice for
children and work to ensure that each child's needs, safety, well-being, and path to a safe and
permanent home remain at the center of the court process; and
WHEREAS, in the most recent reporting year, Louisiana CASA programs served
three thousand seven hundred forty-four children with the support of one thousand four
hundred fourteen CASA volunteers; and
WHEREAS, those CASA volunteers contributed forty-two thousand four hours of
volunteer service, with an estimated value of one million five hundred eighteen thousand
twenty-four dollars; and
