WHEREAS, Louisiana's CASA programs and volunteers merit a special measure of
commendation for their outstanding work on behalf of children and families across the state;
and
WHEREAS, James Barse of CASA Jefferson has been named the Volunteer
Advocate of the Year in recognition of his outstanding commitment, passion, and dedication
to improving the lives of the children he serves; the Volunteer Advocate of the Year Award
recognizes a CASA advocate who has demonstrated exceptional skill in advocating for the
best interests of a CASA child and who has gone above and beyond in the role of CASA
volunteer advocate; and
WHEREAS, Ja'Nika Stanley of Capital Area CASA has been named the Heart of
Advocacy Award recipient in recognition of her resilience, determination, and strength as
a CASA-served former foster youth who rose above difficult circumstances to build a
hopeful and healthy future; and
WHEREAS, CASA Day at the Capitol provides an important opportunity to
recognize the essential role of CASA programs and volunteers in Louisiana's child welfare
and judicial systems and to raise awareness of the continued need for advocacy on behalf of
children.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend the Louisiana Court Appointed Special
Advocate programs across the state and the CASA volunteers who give tirelessly of their
time and energy to serve as powerful voices for children; does hereby recognize and honor
James Barse of CASA Jefferson as the Volunteer Advocate of the Year and Ja'Nika Stanley
of Capital Area CASA as the Heart of Advocacy Award recipient; and does hereby designate
Wednesday, May 27, 2026, as CASA Day at the Capitol and encourages continued support
for CASA programs and the children and families they serve throughout Louisiana.
